item.description:
A good accessibility label lets your customer know exactly what a control does in as few words as possible, without having to rely on implied context.
Don&rsquo;t Add the Element Type iOS already knows your button is a button and your image is an image, it does this using an accessibility trait. If you label your button as &lsquo;Play button&rsquo; your VoiceOver customers will hear &lsquo;Play button. Button.&rsquo;
Keep it Succinct Don&rsquo;t frustrate your customer by adding too much information to your labels.
